</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/6/03 12:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2074.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: All this talk about FF XI...</span><hr size=1> O..M..G..<br>
<br>
Sabrosia, this game is sooo much better than SWG, believe me, I played SWG for about 3 weeks. In that small amount of time, I maxxed my character out. There was nothing more for me to do. I got bored, and tired of paying for a game that should still be in beta, and quit.<br>
<br>
Now, SWG graphically is stunning. and is probably better looking than even Final Fantasy XI. I will make one point, and believe me, there are many..<br>
<br>
In SWG, SOE did do one thing right. The job system is such that if you get tired of being, say, a Master Ranger, you can &quot;unlearn&quot; that skill and start over..without re-rolling..to say, a Artisan or entertainer.<br>
<br>
Final Fantasy XI, topped that. Listen to this...You start out as any of the basic classes you wish. Let's say we start a Monk. I won't even mention the special jobs you can get flagged for ((Paladin, Ninja, Dark Knight, etc)) <br>
<br>
You roll up your monk to say, level 8..or 10, any level really. You can go see your personal Moogle and change jobs! you can work on your White Mage, maybe a little Warrior action..You can level ALL of the jobs all the way to level 70! To keep it balanced, you may only use 2 of them at a time, and even if you have your monk to level 70, if you are using the monk as a sub-job, you can only use the monk skills up to half of the main job you currently have.<br>
<br>
I like that. I think it keeps the game interesting. Today I am a 44Warrior/22 White Mage.<br>
<br>
Hey we are going to kill an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>instanced</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> boss fight! Today I am going to dig out my spell book and be a 55Black Mage/ 24Thief. <br>
<br>
Look, comparing this game to EQ, is not really a good comparison. It is a Final Fantasy game, made to be played with a controller. The game is not easy. The people at Square Enix have put together a wonderful game. There is no lag, and not a single bug to speak of. The developers at Suare are gamers. They put neat things into the game they know that gamers like.<br>
<br>
Imagine you are fishing in the ocean, one day with your lvl 35 monk. There you are catching a fish, then maybe a rusty bucket. Suddenly you feel a tug on your fishing rod. You reel the thing in, and it is a lvl 30'ish Octopus monster..better scramble to get your gear straight as it is getting ready to attack...<br>
<br>
I love Final Fantasy XI<br>
<br>
