<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Sir Cyradus Hateborn</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"> Grave Lord - 61st level of power</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub33.ezboard.com/bleagueofshadows"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">League of shadows</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->-<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=392701"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:yellow;">My gear</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->-<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub219.ezboard.com/bnecropolis"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">The dark city</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theghostwalker>The Ghostwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/6/03 1:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2074.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: All this talk about FF XI...</span><hr size=1> I would have to add my honest agreement to Cy's statement.  The game is much deeper than you might imagine, with control over your character you can only imagine in other games.  Your choice of classes is important - are you the bard with support songs with a white mage subclass to backup heal, or do you go black mage for some nuking... or monk to get in there and mix it up with more damage.<br>
<br>
Item synthesis (tradeskills) is very cool so far, and creates a good market for something readily available to newbies.  The items you can create vary from cure potions to daggers to rings... etc.<br>
<br>
The conquest system is subtle, yet could create cultural conflicts of massive scale.  The entire game is based around missions and quests, and finding groups is dirt simple.  If you don't care who you group with, it's as simple as selecting autogroup.<br>
<br>
In short... there's a lot of depth to be found, if you look for it.  And the players are generally curtious, helpful, and more than willing to buy your crystals for 200gil apiece. ;D<br>
